  "description": "React Form Validator exposes a single React component which uses the render prop pattern to validate the input on its child form.    It is built as a pure React component, with no additional dependencies, making it efficient and cheap to add to any React project. Due to interacting with underlying basic HTML tags, it is compatible with popular design Frameworks like Semantic or Bootstrap out of the box. <!--  The render prop function will be passed `isFormValid`, `isFieldValid`, `errors`, `fields`, and `onChange` to use in the form itself. -->",
